text: Carlos Garcia Camacho (November 16, 1924 â€“ December 6, 1979) was a Guamanian politician and member of the Republican Party. He served as the last appointed Governor of Guam from 1969 to 1971 and the first elected Governor of Guam from 1971 to 1975. Camacho died on December 6, 1979 in Tamunimg, Guam from a heart attack, aged 55. ==References== Category:1924 births Category:1979 deaths Category:Deaths from myocardial infarction Category:Governors of Guam Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
